m_q.target_metric: Count of undefeated fighters per weight class and identification of top fighters in each weight class
sub_questions: How many fighters remain undefeated in each weight class?
Which fighters have the best records in each weight class?
What is the distribution of undefeated fighters across weight classes?

scale_issues: Some percentage columns may exceed 100% (e.g., takedown_accuracy shows 100.0 for multiple fighters)

format_notes: Some fighters have missing reach_in_cm, stance, and date_of_birth values
Weight classes need to be derived from weight_in_kg column

statistical_tests: Verify percentage columns are within 0-100 range
output_format_requirements: Output must be written to undefeated.csv with columns: level, fighter_num
Weight classes need to be standardized (e.g., Lightweight, Welterweight, etc.) from weight_in_kg values
fighter_num likely represents count of undefeated fighters per weight class
